Samantha Lee @Samantha_Lee121 Police are on the hunt for five suspects who managed to escape police custody on Saturday. PHOTO FOR ILLUSTRATION: Samantha lee Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Police are searching for five suspects who managed to escape police custody on Saturday.The five men, aged between 21 and 33 years, were in the Lentegeur police holding cells awaiting their first court appearance for various crimes related to drugs, theft, business robbery and car theft, say police.It is unclear whether the men knew each other.It is believed that the men overpowered a guard and escaped with the keys.All locks have since been replaced. A tracing team is currently looking for the suspects. Anyone with information about their whereabouts can call CrimeStop, says provincial police spokesperson Captain FC van Wyk.An official investigation is currently under way.Mark Brookes, Community Police Forum spokesperson, declined to comment on the specifics of the incident.He does, however, urge residents not to judge police as incompetent. Social media is abuzz with the news, but jail breaks happen. Instead of solutions and asking how they can assist, people are blaming police, says Brookes.At the time of going to print, none of the escapees had been arrested. V If you have any information that can help police, call 08600 10111. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.